<div class="[ o-basic-layout ] {{ animation?'js-animations':'' }}">
    {% include 'includes/sidebar.twig' with{'logoClass': animation?'intro-animation':'', 'menuClass': animation?'intro-animation':''} %}
    <main class="[ c-main ] {{ animation?'intro-animation':'' }}">
        <h2 class="c-page-title">Automatic critical css with twig and PHP.</h2>
        {% include 'includes/sharelinks.twig' %}
        <p>Small php library in combination with a twig extention that allows you to annotate above-the-fold-html in your twig files which will than extract all the necessary CSS.</p>
        <p>In combination with loadCSS you can setup a critcal CSS solution quite easy.</p>

        <h3>Key features</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Automatically generated</li>
            <li>Manual control through <code class="language-twig">{{ '{% fold %}{% endfold %}' }}</code> tags</li>
            <li>Dynamically resolves CSS used on each page</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Demo</h3>
        <p>
            <a rel="noopener" target="_blank" href="/with">/with</a> – <a rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="Benchmark with critical CSS enabled on a slow 3G connection" href="https://www.webpagetest.org/result/170122_VJ_RHE/">benchmark <em>*</em></a> – <em>critical CSS enabled</em><br>
            <a rel="noopener" target="_blank" href="/without">/without</a> – <a rel="noopener" target="_blank" title="Benchmark with critical CSS enabled on a slow 3G connection" href="https://www.webpagetest.org/result/170122_P5_RHH/">benchmark <em>*</em></a> – <em>critical CSS <b>not</b>
                enabled</em>
        </p>
        <p>Take a look at these page sources to see the critical CSS in action.</p>
        <p><em>*</em> These benchmarks are run on a slow 3G connection. This is where critical CSS is the most important.</p>

        <h3 id="usage">Usage</h3>
        <pre class="u-margin-bottom-none">
<code class="language-twig">{% filter e %}
{{ '{% fold %}' }}
    <button class=”your-css-class”>Button</button>
{{ '{% endfold %}' }}{% endfilter %}</code></pre>
<pre class="u-margin-top-none">
<code class="language-markup">{% filter e('html') %}<!-- output -->
<head>
    <style>
        .your-css-class {
            color: pink;
        }
    </style>
</head>{% endfilter %}
</code>
            </pre>
    </main>
</div>